PROMPT dong_zuobin_oracle_bones
WITH BUDGET 4000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a Chinese archaeology and paleography expert specializing in oracle bone studies, early 20th century Chinese scholarship, and the development of oracle bone studies as a modern academic discipline.")

GENERATE
    explain_dong_zuobin("Explain who Dong Zuobin (董作宾) was and his major contributions to oracle bone studies. Cover: 1) His biographical background as a leading Chinese archaeologist, paleographer, and oracle bone scholar (1895-1963), including his academic training and career positions at Academia Sinica, 2) His role in the systematic archaeological excavations at Yinxu (殷墟) starting in 1928, which transformed oracle bone studies from antiquarian collecting to rigorous scientific archaeology, 3) His development of the periodization system for oracle bone inscriptions, establishing chronological phases that allowed scholars to date oracle bones to specific Shang dynasty kings and periods, 4) His pioneering work in oracle bone paleography, including the systematic cataloging and classification of oracle bone characters and their variant forms, 5) His contributions to deciphering previously unknown oracle bone characters and clarifying the meanings of difficult inscriptions, 6) His role in establishing scholarly methodology for oracle bone studies, including standards for excavation documentation, rubbing techniques, and epigraphic analysis, 7) His extensive publications including major catalogs of oracle bone inscriptions and foundational studies that became standard references in the field, 8) His influence in training the next generation of oracle bone scholars and establishing oracle bone studies as a legitimate academic discipline, 9) His work in correlating oracle bone inscriptions with Shang dynasty historical chronology and his contributions to understanding Shang political and social structures, 10) His lasting legacy as one of the founding fathers of modern oracle bone studies alongside scholars like Wang Guowei and Guo Moruo, and how his systematic approach laid the foundation for all subsequent oracle bone research.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 3000 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.1, FORMAT markdown;